## 2. Influencers
These personas provide technical expertise, process governance, or specialized support to guide the decision-making process.

### Technical & Architecture Influencers
* [cite_start]**Technical Leads/SMEs:** Systems Engineers, Network Engineers, DBAs, Cloud/Security Architects [cite: 51-57]. [cite_start]They influence troubleshooting, root cause analysis, and implementation[cite: 14, 15].
* [cite_start]**Head of Engineering/SRE:** Oversees how engineering and IT teams work together; influences how applications are architected for resilience[cite: 97].

### Process & Governance Influencers
* [cite_start]**Problem Manager:** Focuses on root cause analysis (RCA) and long-term preventative measures[cite: 17, 65].
* [cite_start]**Change Manager:** Assesses the impact of proposed changes to minimize disruption during resolution[cite: 18, 69].
* [cite_start]**Head of Operational Resilience:** Manages remediation plans and reports on operational resilience status[cite: 96].

### Communication & Security Influencers
* [cite_start]**Communication Manager:** Shapes the incident narrative and manages stakeholder perceptions[cite: 16, 60].
* [cite_start]**CISO / Head of Cyber Security:** Oversees protection of infrastructure and assets; manages responses to cyber incidents[cite: 97].
* [cite_start]**Head of Security Operations:** Typically runs the Security Operations Center (SOC) and monitors the network for events[cite: 97].

