## 3. Users (Tactical & Affected Parties)
These individuals are the hands-on operators of MIM tools or those directly impacted by the service disruption.

### IT Support & Operations
* [cite_start]**Service Desk Technicians:** Help Desk Analysts, Service Desk Agents[cite: 73, 75]. [cite_start]They are the first point of contact, gathering information and escalating incidents[cite: 19, 20].
* [cite_start]**IT Support Staff:** Systems/Network Administrators, Desktop Support, Field Technicians [cite: 78-82]. [cite_start]They implement fixes, perform diagnostics, and perform the hands-on resolution[cite: 21, 22].

### Business Users
* [cite_start]**End-Users:** Individuals or systems affected by the incident[cite: 23]. [cite_start]While not in the response team, they are the primary reason for the MIM process[cite: 24].
* [cite_start]**Stakeholders:** Department Heads, Business Unit Managers, Project Managers [cite: 85-89]. [cite_start]They receive updates and make business decisions based on the incident’s impact[cite: 25, 26].

